Dear mom, 

I feel like we haven’t caught up in a while but I’ve been living by your words and staying true to myself and what “be happy” means to me. I just came back home from a 2 week solo trip to my dream destination to Japan and can’t wait to share with you all the photos and videos I got. I know how much you loved taking photos and that’s probably where I got it from. But I’m so proud of myself for navigating a new country all by myself and hope you are as well. I know you would’ve loved to see Europe one day so maybe that’s where I’ll go next, for us. I saw you in a dream the day before my birthday and maybe that was your way of visiting me. Thanks for checking in on me and making me not feel so alone on my solo trip. I can’t wait to share with you more adventures and know you’ll visit me on those ones too. Love you so much and Happy Mother’s Day ❤️

2 weeks ago I started my solo trip. To me it was more than a vacation. I sought after a challenge, a new experience to help me grow and love myself in new ways I couldn’t before without stepping outside of my comfort zone. I can whole heartedly say it truly fulfilled my soul to no end.

Proud of myself for being scared to embark on a new country, language and culture alone but fearless enough to take it head on and conquer it all. The journey wasn’t always smooth sailing but by embracing it all, that’s how you learn and grow and I want to be the best possible version of myself I can for myself.

Knowing that I can find happiness within myself and not from someone or something else is rewarding knowing how hard I worked to get to this feeling. Gave myself the world I deserve and will never settle for anything less.
A flawless trip indeed 💕

Felt like a pretty flower last night 🌹

Princess of Japan 🌸 Being able to wear a kimono around Kyoto and appreciating the culture was such an experience for me. This was not a part of my itinerary but I decided to try it out last minute. The women that dolled me up allowed me to express my femininity in a way I never knew I could before. They were so respectful of my gender identity and allowed me to use either the women’s or private dressing room. Never knew my hair could get this voluminous and wearing my two favorite colors pink and green was a dream. Befriended some ladies when they asked to take photos of me and we explored Kyoto together. I felt like I was about to be a bride and never felt prettier. Thank you @rentalkimonookamoto for the experience. Truly a core memory 💗💚

Wearing a kimono being trans! Such an experience getting all dolled up in Japan’s culture 🌸 Thank you to @rentalkimonookamoto for taking me in 💚

Today marks 5 years since my mother Linda passed away from ovarian cancer back in 2018. I was 22 at the time, and my pain felt like it would never go away and linger with me forever. Now at 27, I live with strength and confidence as I strive for happiness each day per my mother’s wishes in a letter she wrote. 

Here are 5 things I wish she got to experience with me but know she’s watching 💕

2019- Landed a year long relationship with Sephora in their first ever Sephora Squad 💄
2020- Moved out at 23 to LA 🌴
2021- Bought a house at 24 in California 🏠
2022- Had my first surgery being a hair transplant 🤕
2023- Embarked on my solo travel journey starting with my dream destination to Japan 🇯🇵 

Here’s to living life to the fullest and growing to be better versions of ourselves each year. Love and miss you Mama Flawless ❤️

Surprising my dad that I’m on Squid Game 💚 

I sent in an audition tape over a year ago during a time when I was facing burn out in hopes of finding a new opportunity to step outside my comfort zone and grow. My family was also in mind and I saw this as a chance for me to give back to the people that had sacrificed so much. My mom passed in 2018 from ovarian cancer and my dad was supporting my sister and her college education by himself. This was my way of repaying them after a lifetime of love and support in hopes of being the winner of the $4.56 prize. Regardless of if I was the winner or not, being casted was an accomplishment within itself that I know my dad and mom are very proud of 💕

My Squid Game: The Challenge audition tape! June 2022, I sent in this video for the casting call for one of my greatest adventures yet. This was at a time I was facing burn out from creating content during my Homophobes Era. Feeling uninspired I thought why not send in an audition tape as I had nothing to lose. Little did I know this era would kickstart a new found confidence within me. This was before my solo travels, before acting classes, before my hair transplant and before navigating my gender identity even deeper. Because of Squid Game, I’m a stronger version of myself than the one in this video. Thank you to all of my friends and family for the love and support; who have been on this journey with me from behind the scenes. And thank you to @producer.surfer.dad.superhero for believing in me and the value I had to offer to the world. Regardless of the outcome, this experience was truly a once in a lifetime moment that I’m forever grateful to be a part of. I just know this is the beginning and there is something greater out there for me 💚

Thank you 2023 💕 Such a transformative year of personal and professional growth that introduced the solo travel and Squid Game era which gave me newfound inspiration and confidence to create content and occupy space in this world as a trans POC. Kicked off the year in London filming the Netflix reality show Squid Game: The Challenge then transitioned to New York before taking on my dream destination of Japan followed by South Korea. If there’s one thing I’ve learned from my mom and travels, it’s that life is too short and do whatever it takes to be happy even if doing it alone. Step outside your comfort zone; you might just make a few friends along the way. Cannot wait for our next adventure in 2024 ❤️
